Approach 3: Sorting + Two Pointers
Intuition

Sort the array.

Use two pointers:

left → smallest element
right → largest element

If:

Sum == k → pair found
Sum < k → move left
Sum > k → move right
Java
class Solution {
    public int maxOperations(int[] nums, int k) {

        Arrays.sort(nums);

        int left = 0;
        int right = nums.length - 1;
        int count = 0;

        while (left < right) {

            int sum = nums[left] + nums[right];

            if (sum == k) {
                count++;
                left++;
                right--;
            }
            else if (sum < k) {
                left++;
            }
            else {
                right--;
            }
        }

        return count;
    }
}
